-- Canadian Solar to Supply 32 Megawatts of Panels for China Plant
-- B y   J u s t i n   D o o m
-- 2013-11-12T15:32:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-11-12/canadian-solar-to-supply-32-megawatts-of-panels-for-china-plant.html
Canadian Solar Inc. (CSIQ) , the best-performing solar manufacturer this year, agreed to supply 32
megawatts of panels for a project in  China .  Delivery to China Perfect Machinery Industry Corp. will be
completed this month, the Guelph, Ontario-based solar
manufacturer said today in a statement. Terms weren’t disclosed.  “Demand for solar modules in China is picking up nicely in
the fourth quarter,” Canadian Solar Chief Executive Officer
Shawn Qu said in the statement. The company is scheduled to
report its third-quarter earnings tomorrow, and said Nov. 4 it’s
expecting its first quarterly profit in more than two years.  Canadian Solar has increased more than eightfold this year,
the most in the 15-member Bloomberg Industries Global Large
Solar Index.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Justin Doom in  New York  at 
